text.tspan: Rate of disease burden from eating disorders by age, World, 1990 to 2019
Disease burden is measured in Disability-Adjusted Life Years (DALYs). This is given per 100,000 individuals.
DALYs are used to measure total burden of disease - both from years of life lost and years lived with a disability.
One DALY equals one lost year of healthy life.
Data source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease (2019)
